OL,3,C'Hero' rescues disabled man from
OL,4,C'fireball' car
OL,6,FAfter she got out of the car, Michael
OL,7,FGadiner, who was passing, noticed she
OL,8,Fwas in trouble and dragged Garry to
OL,9,Fsafety seconds before the car was
OL,10,Fengulfed in flames.
OL,12,FJulie described Mr Gardiner as "my
OL,13,Fhero" adding: "I don't think I would
OL,14,Fhave been able to get Garry out on my
OL,15,Fown. He definitely saved us.
OL,17,F"If we had gone any further I think
OL,18,Fwe'd have gone up in a ball of flames."
