OL,3,C'Hero' rescues disabled man from
OL,4,C'fireball' car
OL,6,F"I remember people helping and
OL,7,Fgrabbing (Garry) out. As they grabbed
OL,8,Fhim out I looked at the front and the
OL,9,Fwheels were on fire... We started
OL,10,Fmoving away and as I turned around
OL,11,Fagain it was a fireball."
OL,13,FMr Gardiner, a chef at a New Farnley
OL,14,FCricket Club, helped with another man
OL,15,Fto pull Garry from the car.
OL,17,FHe said he was "thankful we there just
OL,18,Fat the right time".
OL,20,F"It all happened so quick - two
OL,21,Fminutes," he said.
